Below is an example code snippet to create a 'Matrix'-themed text page with green 0/1 falling endlessly.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
	<title>Matrix Themed Page</title>
	<style type="text/css">
		body {
			background-color: black;
			overflow: hidden;
		}

		.matrix-text {
			font-family: monospace;
			color: green;
			position: absolute;
			font-size: 2em;
			pointer-events: none;
		}
	</style>
</head>
<body>
	<div class="matrix-text"></div>

	<script>
		const text = '01101000 01100101 01101100 01101100 01101111 00101100 00100000 01110111 01101111 01110010 01101100 01100100 00100001 ';
		let index = 0;
		const speed = 50;
		let matrixTextElement = document.querySelector('.matrix-text');

		function startAnimation() {
			let letterToDisplay = text[index];
			matrixTextElement.innerText += letterToDisplay;

			if (index < text.length - 1) {
				index++;
			} else {
				index = 0;
				matrixTextElement.innerText = '';
			}

			setTimeout(startAnimation, speed);
		}

		startAnimation();
	</script>
</body>
</html>
```

The script animates the falling green 0/1 text with the help of the `setTimeout` method, which calls the `startAnimation` function every `speed` milliseconds. The text is stored in the `text` variable and the `matrix-text` class is used to add the green color and font styling to the text. The `overflow: hidden` property of the body element hides the overflow of the text.
